title: Average Number of Persons per Primary Health Care Centre, Darfur, Before and After NGOs expulsion 3.13.2009
name: Average Number of Persons per Primary Health Care Centre, Darfur, Before and After NGOs expulsion 3.13.2009
description:
This dataset shows the average number of persons per Primary Health Care Centres in administrative boundaries with Darfur in Sudan. The rates are from before March 13th 2009 and after March 13th 2009. The two different times are recorded to show the impact that the expulsions of several NGOs throughout Dafur by the Sudanese government has had on healthcare in the region.

The map is from the World Health Organization (WHO)

Values of Zero (admin boundaries with no health care coverage) are given a value of 500,000 for mapping purposes.
